Step 1: Identify the quick assets. Quick assets include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, and Accounts Receivable. In this problem, they are provided as follows:
 • Cash on Hand: 2,103,508.95  
 • Bank Deposits: 4,714,000.00  
 • Interest Receivable: 15,414.09  
 • Accounts Receivable: 3,149,338.94

Step 2: Sum the quick assets:
 2,103,508.95 + 4,714,000.00 = 6,817,508.95  
 6,817,508.95 + 15,414.09 = 6,832,923.04  
 6,832,923.04 + 3,149,338.94 = 9,982,261.98

Step 3: Identify the total current liabilities:
 Total Current Liabilities = 499,821.72

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio:
 Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
 Quick Ratio = 9,982,261.98 / 499,821.72 ≈ 19.96

Thus, the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 19.96.
